<p>Soleimani, 62, was <a href="https://www.washingtonexaminer.com/policy/defense-national-security/irans-infamous-shadow-general-qassem-soleimani-killed-in-air-strike">killed in a U.S. drone strike</a> in Baghdad on Friday, along with Abu Mahdi al Muhandis, who led the Iranian-backed Popular Mobilization Forces. </p>
<p class="">Soleimani was responsible for the deaths of more than 600 
U.S. troops during the Iraq War as the commander of the Quds Force, a 
branch of the Islamic Revolutionary Guard Corps responsible for special 
operations in other countries.</p>
